import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load data
data = pd.read_json('income.json')

# Box plot of income by age group
sns.set(style="whitegrid")
ax = sns.boxplot(x="age_group", y="income", data=data, palette="Set3")
ax.set(xlabel='Age Group', ylabel='Income')
plt.title('What is the distribution of income across different age groups?', wrap=True)

# Show plot
plt.show()
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load data
data = pd.read_json('income.json')

# Plot histogram of income by gender
sns.histplot(data=data, x='income', hue='gender', multiple='stack', kde=True)
plt.axvline(data['income'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median Income')
plt.legend(title='Gender')
plt.title('What is the distribution of income by gender?')

# Show plot
plt.show()
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load data
data = pd.read_json('income.json')

# Plot scatter plot of income by occupation
sns.scatterplot(x='occupation', y='income', data=data)

# Set chart title
plt.title('What is the relationship between income and occupation?', wrap=True)

# Set x-axis label rotation
plt.xticks(rotation=90)

# Show plot
plt.show()

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load data
data = pd.read_json('income.json')

# Box plot of income by race
sns.set(style="whitegrid")
ax = sns.boxplot(x="race", y="income", data=data, palette="Set3")
ax.set_title('What is the distribution of income by race?')

# Add median line
medians = data.groupby(['race'])['income'].median().values
median_labels = [f'{v:,.2f}' for v in medians]
pos = range(len(medians))
for tick,label in zip(pos,ax.get_xticklabels()):
    ax.text(pos[tick], medians[tick] + 0.03, median_labels[tick], 
            horizontalalignment='center', size='x-small', color='black', weight='semibold')
    ax.axhline(medians[tick], color='black', linestyle='--', alpha=0.4)

plt.show()
```
